{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-template-js","path":"/notes/Colourful-output-in-R-in-terminal","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Actually after searching, there are indeed some ways to achive this, merely contributed by <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29861065/coloring-output-in-r-language\">this StackOverflow</a>.</p>\n<h2>1. Directly use Colour Index</h2>\n<p>I can directly output some colour with some simple code:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"r\"><pre class=\"language-r\"><code class=\"language-r\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>col <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"token number\">29</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token number\">47</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    cat<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>paste0<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0;\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> col<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> txt<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0m  \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1000px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/c0ebd/figure4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 2.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAABCAYAAADeko4lAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAWUlEQVQI1w3FwQ1AMABAUWM4OIggoqmGlqZB0ksxgBWczOZqBVOY5fMuLypFg6kGdOFQOmFeYoSoWdftXxBCQEqJ9x5rLYMxtG7mnHLeo2P0Kf3dI/eM51J8E8AivyIPersAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"catsolution\"\n        title=\"catsolution\"\n        src=\"/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/00d43/figure4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/63868/figure4.png 250w,\n/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/0b533/figure4.png 500w,\n/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/00d43/figure4.png 1000w,\n/static/d79982bced960ba12f3f0b140a1d4a29/c0ebd/figure4.png 1177w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>So I would prefer some below colours:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"r\"><pre class=\"language-r\"><code class=\"language-r\"><span class=\"token operator\">></span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>paste0<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0;41m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">' Error Message '</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">></span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>paste0<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0;43m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">' Warning Message '</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">></span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>paste0<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0;44m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">' Code Example: print(\"Hello World!\") '</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\\033[0m\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 831px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f45954d45512f62be81c8ab7d7286463/5b4a1/figure2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 23.599999999999998%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Some useful colours\"\n        title=\"Some useful colours\"\n        src=\"/static/f45954d45512f62be81c8ab7d7286463/5b4a1/figure2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f45954d45512f62be81c8ab7d7286463/63868/figure2.png 250w,\n/static/f45954d45512f62be81c8ab7d7286463/0b533/figure2.png 500w,\n/static/f45954d45512f62be81c8ab7d7286463/5b4a1/figure2.png 831w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>2. Use R package</h2>\n<p>A nice package <a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/crayon/index.html\">crayon</a> is designed for this purpose, I will not use it simply because I don't want to wrap too many pacakges into ChAMP, but it's indeed a good solution for people who have this purpose.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"r\"><pre class=\"language-r\"><code class=\"language-r\">library<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>crayon<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\ncat<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>blue<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"world!\\n\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 337px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5b7fdf623863868310ca516b9e3db051/f6b51/figure3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"crayon\"\n        title=\"crayon\"\n        src=\"/static/5b7fdf623863868310ca516b9e3db051/f6b51/figure3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5b7fdf623863868310ca516b9e3db051/63868/figure3.png 250w,\n/static/5b7fdf623863868310ca516b9e3db051/f6b51/figure3.png 337w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 337px) 100vw, 337px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"December 30, 2020","slug":"/notes/Colourful-output-in-R-in-terminal","title":"Colourful output in R in terminal","abstract":"I am recently improving ChAMP, I hope to improve the message output for ChAMP a bit. More specifically, I hope the print to be better formated, and with 2-3 coloures styles to indicates important message or code snippers. Finally I found some ways to do this."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/notes/Colourful-output-in-R-in-terminal"}}}